-- French Stocks: BNP Paribas, Nexans, Vinci Shares Move in Paris Trading
-- David Altaner
-- 2010-08-02T15:48:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/areva-eurazeo-nexans-france-telecom-rexel-vinci-french-stock-preview.html

          
          
             France’s benchmark CAC 40 Index rose
108.89, or 3 percent, to 3.752.03 at the 5:30 p.m. close in
Paris. The SBF 120 Index gained 2.8 percent.  
 The following stocks were among the most active in the
French equity market. Stock symbols are in parentheses after
company names.  
 BNP Paribas  (BNP FP) rose 5.3 percent to 55.49 euros, a
three-month high. France’s biggest bank said second-quarter
profit gained 31 percent as bad-loan provisions declined.  
 Nexans SA  (NEX FP) gained 2.4 percent to 53.31 euros. The
world’s biggest maker of cables and wires expects to increase
revenue and profitability in the second half of the year, even
as the company faces uncertainty about production of underwater
cables, Journal des Finances reported, citing an interview with
Chief Executive Officer Frederic Vincent.  
 Vinci SA  (DG FP) rose 3.7 percent to 38.54 euros, the
largest gain in more than two months. The world’s biggest
builder and partners won a contract to build and operate a new
airport at Notre-Dame-des-Landes in western France, the
government said.  
